<p>Every property investor in Melaka faces the same dilemma: Do I sign a 1-year tenancy agreement (Long-Term Rental) or turn my unit into a vacation home (Short-Term Rental / Airbnb)?</p>

<p>Both strategies have pros and cons. Let's break down the financials and operational realities for 2026.</p>

<h2>1. Financial Returns (ROI)</h2>

<h3>Long-Term Rental (LTR)</h3>
<p><strong>Pros:</strong> Consistent monthly income. Once a tenant signs, you know exactly what you'll get for the next year.</p>
<p><strong>Cons:</strong> Lower ceiling. In Melaka, rental yields for condos typically hover around <strong>3-4%</strong>. You can't raise rent mid-lease even if market rates skyrocket.</p>

